    'duration': 'Concentration, up to 1 minute',
    'description': '<p>You touch a creature, and that creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become cursed for the duration of the spell. When you cast this spell, choose the nature of the curse from the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Choose one ability score. While cursed, the target has disadvantage on ability checks and saving throws made with that ability score.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>While cursed, the target has disadvantage on attack rolls against you.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>While cursed, the target must make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of each of its turns. If it fails, it wastes its action that turn doing nothing.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>While the target is cursed, your attacks and spells deal an extra 1d8 necrotic damage to the target.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A <a href="http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:remove-curse">Remove Curse</a> spell ends this effect. At the DM&#8217;s option, you may choose an alternative curse effect, but it should be no more powerful than those described above. The DM has final say on such a curse&#8217;s effect.</p>',
